All tested common username and password pairs (admin:admin, root:toor, user:user, toor:toor) failed to log in via SSH on port 22022.

Next plan:
- Try an SSH banner grabbing with Netcat to see if there are any clues about SSH configuration or version.
- Explore alternative entry points by scanning the target with a TCP connect scan with version detection on other uncommon ports (e.g., 1-1024) to see if any services might be overlooked.

First, banner grab using netcat on port 22022.

Executing:  
echo | nc -v 172.10.0.3 22022 -w 2

The SSH banner on port 22022 reveals the service is "SSH-2.0-Go".

Next, perform a TCP connect scan with version detection for ports 1-1024 to find any other open services possibly overlooked.

nmap -sT -sV -p1-1024 -T3 172.10.0.3 -oG -
